TITLE: Implementing Factorial with For-Loop in Solidity - Solidity
DESCRIPTION: Implements a factorial function using a for-loop in Solidity. The function accepts a uint256 integer parameter and returns its factorial. Edge cases (0 and 1) return 1 directly; for greater numbers, the result is calculated iteratively. Requires only Solidity standard types, with 'num' as input and its factorial as output. Constraints: valid for non-negative integers, may overflow for large inputs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/academy/solidity-foundry/05-hello-world-part-2/02-control-flow.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: solidity
CODE:
```
function factorial(uint256 num) public pure returns(uint256) {\n    if (num == 0) {\n      return 1;\n    } else if (num == 1) {\n      return 1;\n    }\n    uint256 result = num;\n    for (uint i = 2; i < num; i++) {\n      result = result * i;\n    }\n    return result;\n}
```

