TITLE: Creating Stateful Precompiled Contract for Calculator Plus in Go
DESCRIPTION: This function creates a stateful precompiled contract with calculator-like operations. It maps ABI functions to their implementations, creates precompile functions, and constructs the final contract without a fallback function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/academy/customizing-evm/08-calculator-precompile/02-generating-precompile.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: Go
CODE:
```
func createCalculatorplusPrecompile() contract.StatefulPrecompiledContract {
    var functions []*contract.StatefulPrecompileFunction

    abiFunctionMap := map[string]contract.RunStatefulPrecompileFunc{
        "moduloPlus": moduloPlus,
        "powOfThree": powOfThree,
        "simplFrac":  simplFrac,
    }

    for name, function := range abiFunctionMap {
        method, ok := CalculatorplusABI.Methods[name]
        if !ok {
            panic(fmt.Errorf("given method (%s) does not exist in the ABI", name))
        }
        functions = append(functions, contract.NewStatefulPrecompileFunction(method.ID, function))
    }
    // Construct the contract with no fallback function.
    statefulContract, err := contract.NewStatefulPrecompileContract(nil, functions)
    if err != nil {
        panic(err)
    }
    return statefulContract
}
```

