TITLE: Fetching Recent Blocks with AvaCloud SDK in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This function fetches the 20 most recent blocks using the AvaCloud SDK's Data API. It iterates through paginated results and combines them into a single array of EvmBlock objects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/academy/avacloudapis/06-block-explorer-app/03-modifying-code.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const getRecentBlocks = async () => {
    const result = await avaCloudSDK.data.evm.blocks.getLatestBlocks({
        pageSize: 1,
      });

    let count = 0;
    const blocks: EvmBlock[] = [];
    for await (const page of result) {
        if (count === 20) {
            break;
        }
        blocks.push(...page.result.blocks);
        count++;
    }
    return blocks
}
```

