TITLE: Implementing Block Rejection in TimestampVM
DESCRIPTION: The reject function marks a block as rejected in the VM state. It updates the block's status, persists it to storage, and removes it from the verified blocks collection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/docs/virtual-machines/timestamp-vm/blocks.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
/// Mark this [`Block`](Block) rejected and updates `State` (crate::state::State) accordingly.
/// # Errors
/// Returns an error if the state can't be updated.
pub async fn reject(&mut self) -> io::Result<()> {
    self.set_status(choices::status::Status::Rejected);

    // only decided blocks are persistent -- no reorg
    self.state.write_block(&self.clone()).await?;

    self.state.remove_verified(&self.id()).await;
    Ok(())
}
```

