TITLE: Implementing Block Acceptance in TimestampVM
DESCRIPTION: The accept function marks a block as accepted in the VM state. It updates the block's status, persists it to storage, updates the last accepted block reference, and removes it from the verified blocks collection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/docs/virtual-machines/timestamp-vm/blocks.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: rust
CODE:
```
/// Mark this [`Block`](Block) accepted and updates `State` (crate::state::State) accordingly.
/// # Errors
/// Returns an error if the state can't be updated.
pub async fn accept(&mut self) -> io::Result<()> {
    self.set_status(choices::status::Status::Accepted);

    // only decided blocks are persistent -- no reorg
    self.state.write_block(&self.clone()).await?;
    self.state.set_last_accepted_block(&self.id()).await?;

    self.state.remove_verified(&self.id()).await;
    Ok(())
}
```

