TITLE: Example JSON RPC Call using Curl (X-Chain getTxStatus)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to make a JSON RPC 2.0 call to the `avm.getTxStatus` method of the X-Chain API using the `curl` command-line tool. It sends a POST request with a JSON payload specifying the `jsonrpc` version, a unique request `id`, the target `method` (`avm.getTxStatus`), and the required `params` (the `txID`). The request targets a local node's X-Chain endpoint.
