TITLE: Creating AWS Devnet with Custom VM using Avalanche-CLI Flags in Bash
DESCRIPTION: Creates an Avalanche Devnet named `<clusterName>` on AWS, deploying a custom VM based Avalanche L1 named `<blockchainName>` (e.g., MorpheusVM built with HyperSDK). It uses flags to specify the custom VM details (`--custom-subnet`, repository URL, branch, build script), configuration files (`--subnet-genesis`, `--chain-config`, `--subnet-config`, `--node-config`), cloud provider details (`--aws`), node counts (`--num-apis`, `--num-validators`), regions, validator parameters (`--default-validator-params`), node type (`--node-type default`), and authorizes SSH access (`--authorize-access`). This non-interactive command bypasses the wizard prompts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/docs/tooling/create-avalanche-nodes/setup-devnet.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
avalanche node devnet wiz <clusterName> <blockchainName> --custom-subnet \
  --subnet-genesis <genesisPath> --custom-vm-repo-url <repoUrl> \
  --custom-vm-branch <branch> --custom-vm-build-script <buildScript> \
  --chain-config <chainConfigPath> --subnet-config <subnetConfigPath> \
  --node-config <avagoConfigPath> --authorize-access --aws --num-apis 1,1,1,1,1 \
  --num-validators 5,5,5,5,5  --region us-west-2,us-east-1,ap-south-1,ap-northeast-1,eu-west-1 \
  --default-validator-params --node-type default

Creating the subnet
...
Creating the devnet
...
