TITLE: Calling a SHA256 Precompiled Contract from Solidity
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to interface with and call a SHA256 precompiled contract from a Solidity smart contract. The code defines an interface for the SHA256 precompile, instantiates it with a specific address (0x030...01), and calls its hashing function. The actual implementation exists in Go rather than Solidity.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/common/evm-precompiles/precompiles.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: solidity
CODE:
