TITLE: Calculating L1 Validator Fee Rate (LaTeX/Math)
DESCRIPTION: Presents the mathematical formulas used to determine the L1 validator fee rate per second, as defined in ACP-77. The primary formula calculates the fee based on a minimum price (M), an exponential function (`exp`), a variable 'x' reflecting validator supply vs. target, and a constant 'K' controlling price sensitivity. The secondary formula updates 'x' each second based on the difference between the current number of active validators (V) and the target number (T), ensuring 'x' remains non-negative.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/guides/l1-validator-fee.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: latex
CODE:
```
M \cdot \exp\left(\frac{x}{K}\right)
```

LANGUAGE: latex
CODE:
```
x = \max(x + V - T, 0)
```

