TITLE: Importing Keystore User with AvalancheGo API - Shell
DESCRIPTION: This shell snippet shows how to import a previously exported keystore user into an AvalancheGo node by POSTing a keystore.importUser JSON-RPC call via curl. The json data must include username, password, user (the previously exported hex), and the optional encoding parameter. The API operates only on a node under local control and is deprecated from v1.9.12. Returns an empty object on success.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/docs/api-reference/keystore-api.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: sh
CODE:
```
curl -X POST --data '{
    "jsonrpc":"2.0",
    "id"     :1,
    "method" :"keystore.importUser",
    "params" :{
        "username":"myUsername",
        "password":"myPassword",
        "user"    :"0x7655a29df6fc2747b0874e1148b423b954a25fcdb1f170d0ec8eb196430f7001942ce55b02a83b1faf50a674b1e55bfc000000008cf2d869"
    }
}' -H 'content-type:application/json;' 127.0.0.1:9650/ext/keystore
```

