TITLE: Proto SECP256K1 Transfer Input Specification in Coreth
DESCRIPTION: Protocol buffer message definition for a SECP256K1TransferInput in Coreth. Specifies fields for type ID (4 bytes), amount (8 bytes), and a repeated field for address indices with variable size.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/docs/api-reference/c-chain/txn-format.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: text
CODE:
```
message SECP256K1TransferInput {
    uint32 typeID = 1;                   // 04 bytes
    uint64 amount = 2;                   // 08 bytes
    repeated uint32 address_indices = 3; // 04 bytes + 04 bytes * len(address_indices)
}
```

