TITLE: Basic TestCalculatorRun Function Implementation in Go
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the basic implementation of TestCalculatorRun that runs through predefined unit tests. It iterates through test cases defined in the tests variable and executes each one.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/academy/customizing-evm/08-calculator-precompile/10-fuzz-tests.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
// TestCalculatorEmptyRun tests the Run function of the precompile contract.
func TestCalculatorRun(t *testing.T) {
    // Run tests.
    for name, test := range tests {
        t.Run(name, func(t *testing.T) {
            test.Run(t, Module, state.NewTestStateDB(t))
        })
    }
}
```

