TITLE: Verifying Avalanche CLI Installation with Command-Line (Bash)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to verify if the Avalanche CLI is properly installed within a hosted environment by running 'avalanche -h' in the terminal. It expects the Avalanche CLI to be pre-installed or otherwise accessible from the terminal, with no additional parameters required. The command outputs the CLI's help menu, confirming successful installation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ava-labs/builders-hub.git/blob/master/content/common/avalanche-starter-kit/set-up.mdx#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Bash
CODE:
```
avalanche -h
```

